{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe single `state[\"signature\"]` slot is last-writer-wins, so one kind clobbers another.\nThis is the root-cause fix and the riskiest slice (back-compat + compaction), done first.\n## What\nAdd `state[\"attestations\"]`, a kind-keyed map applied per-key-LWW like\n`process_workflow_run`. `process_signature` writes BOTH `state[\"attestations\"][kind] =\nrecord` AND maintains `state[\"signature\"]` as a LIVE mirror of the MOST-RECENT attestation\n(last SIGNATURE event wins) in live compiled state — so the four existing\n`state.get(\"signature\")` consumers (`signing.verify_signature`, the close-gate path,\n`fsck`/validate, retire_attested_pin) keep working unchanged in this slice, and the\nSNAPSHOT/rollback mirror is automatic. Kind is from the SIGNED `manifest[0]` (substring\nbefore first \":\"); `data[\"kind\"]` is only a hint, used iff it matches, else ignored; a\nblank/unkindable manifest is ignored for routing. Read fold-in: an OLD SNAPSHOT carrying\nonly `signature` (no `attestations`) is folded into the map on restore. Also add\n`state[\"last_reopened_at\"]`: `process_status` records the most recent `closed -> open`\ntransition timestamp (from pre-update status == \"closed\" and target == \"open\"; null if\nnever), so `compute_validity` can check \"not reopened since signed_at\" purely from compiled\nstate. Update `_present.py` `public_state()` with a DEDICATED `attestations` branch that\nstrips the `signature` (HMAC hex) subkey from each per-kind record (the flat\n`_INTERNAL_SUBKEYS` cannot express a wildcard kind level); retain the legacy single-`signature`\nstrip. 114f owns the canonical per-record shape.\n## Scope\n`src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py` (`process_signature`, `process_status`,\n`process_snapshot` fold-in), `src/rebar/reducer/_present.py`, `src/rebar/reducer/_state.py`\n(base-state default), `src/rebar/_commands/compact.py` (mirror is automatic via reduce),\n`ticket_state.schema.json`. No change to the signed payload.\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `attestations` map added; `process_signature` writes `attestations[kind]` AND keeps the live `state[\"signature\"]` most-recent mirror; routing by authoritative `manifest[0]` (data[\"kind\"] only as validated hint).\n- [ ] `state[\"last_reopened_at\"]` records the most recent closed->open timestamp (null if never reopened).\n- [ ] Old-snapshot read fold-in: `signature` -> `attestations` on restore; post-snapshot SIGNATURE events replay into the map; new SNAPSHOTs carry both.\n- [ ] `public_state()` dedicated `attestations` branch strips the HMAC hex from EVERY per-kind record; legacy single-`signature` strip retained; no hex in show/MCP.\n- [ ] Compaction/SNAPSHOT round-trips all kinds; empty `attestations` omitted from `show`/state.\n## Edge cases (pinned)\n- FOLD-IN KIND: the legacy `state[\"signature\"]` record carries its own manifest; fold it\n  into `attestations` under the kind derived from THAT record's `manifest[0]`. If the\n  folded record's manifest is blank/unkindable, DROP it (do not file under a sentinel).\n- RETIREMENT / BLANK EVENTS: `process_signature` treats a SIGNATURE event with an empty\n  manifest OR `retired=True` as a NO-OP — it touches NEITHER `attestations` NOR the\n  `signature` mirror. New code no longer writes such events (929e removes\n  retire_attested_pin); a LEGACY retirement event replayed from an old log is correctly\n  superseded by `last_reopened_at` + validity-on-read (the reopen, not the retirement\n  event, invalidates the prior attestation). Net: a reopened legacy ticket keeps its real\n  attestation records in the map but they read NOT-valid via compute_validity — same gate\n  outcome as the old blank-clear, with no clobber.\n## Acceptance Criteria (edge cases)\n- [ ] Fold-in files the legacy record under its manifest-derived kind; blank/unkindable legacy record is dropped.\n- [ ] A retirement/blank SIGNATURE event is a no-op for both `attestations` and the mirror; a reopened legacy ticket's attestation reads not-valid via validity-on-read (no clobber, same gate outcome)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782794887485315001,"uuid":"8bdfa879-9c20-4e1b-b570-e9badbac9601"}